(224, 1, '2017-07-02 21:30:48', '2017-07-02 21:30:48', 'MADE OF BRASS IN A WOODEN CASE. INSTRUCTIONS ARE PRINTED IN OLD ENGLISH. BRASS RIVETS WERE USED IN THE CASE. A NAIL WAS USED AS A HINGE. THE ORIGINAL HINGE WAS PROBABLY BROKEN AND LOST. BELONGED TO THOMAS STEELE BROUGHT FROM ENGLAND BEFORE 1850\r\nGIVEN BY EDITH SHELLY &amp; IDA SHELLY WAGSTAFF\r\nWRITTEN INSIDE: THE TURN TO BE AT THE END FOR A GUINEA, THE OTHER WAY FOR HALF A GUINEA, AND THE SLIDE AT THE CYPHER, WHERE IT WILL SLOP. IT FLOPS SEVERAL TIMES IN REMOVING TOWARDS THE CENTER, EACH A FARTHING ABOVE THE STANDARD. WHEN GOLD IS SHORT OF WEIGHT, REMOVE THE SLIDE THE OTHER WAY, WHERE EVERY DIVILION IS A PENNY. THESE BALANCES ARE AS ACCURATE AS THE BEST SCALES, MORE EXPEDITIOUS, PORTABLE, AND NOT SO LIABLE TO BE OUT OF ORDER. IF EVER THEY VARY FROM THE STANDARD; THEY ARE SOON RECTIFIED BY THE SLIDE.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8080/wp/item/gold-scale/rsz_atf49/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-225\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-225\" src=\"http://localhost:8080/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/rsz_atf49-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\r\n\r\nAF:84:718 CASE # 5 PICTURE 49 ATF#49', 'GOLD SCALE', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'gold-scale', '', '', '2017-07-02 21:30:48', '2017-07-02 21:30:48', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8080/wp/?post_type=item&#038;p=224', 0, 'item', '', 0),
