(958, 1, '2017-07-03 23:59:07', '2017-07-03 23:59:07', '. ON THE BACK OF THE PICTURE IT SAYS “MARRIAGE PICTURE OF RUFUS JESSE STICE AND ALICE SPEARS STICE TAKEN IN THE CITY OF OMAHA, NEBRASKA. NOVEMBER 12, 1900. MR STICE WAS RAILROAD AGENT IN AMERICAN FORK FOR THE OREGON SHORT LINE RAILROAD. NOW U. P. FOR TWENTY THREE YEARS 1915 – 1938. HE BEGAN HIS SERVICE WITH THE RAILROAD COMPANY IN MISSOURI, LANCASTER, WHERE HE WAS BORN IN 1872. LATER HE CAME WEST AND TOOK A RAILROAD JOB IN GRANGER, WYOMING. HE LIKED LIVING OUT WEST SO HE SENT FOR HIS SWEETHEART, ALICE SPEAR AND MET HER IN OMAHA TO BE WED. HE HELD POSITIONS IN VARIOUS STATIONS FOR THE UNION PACIFIC BEING SENT FINALLY TO LEHI CITY THE AMERICAN FORK IN 1916. WHEN HE RETIRED FROM HIS LABOR WITH THE COMPANY, HE MOVED HIS FAMILY TO LEHI WHERE HIS WIFE\'S FOLKS LIVED WHO HAD COME FROM THE EAST. (KEOKUCK, IOWA) IN THE MIGRATION. THEY ALL JOINED THE CHURCH OF LATTER-DAY SAINTS AND REMAINED IN LEHI WHERE MRS STICE DIED IN 1943. ALICE STICE WAS BORN IN LANGCASTER, MISSOURI AUGUST 17, 1870? AND NOW RESIDES AT LEHI IN HER FOLKS HOME.”\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8080/wp/item/a-picture-of-a-wedding-couple/rsz_atf1175/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-959\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-959\" src=\"http://localhost:8080/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/rsz_atf1175-213x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"213\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\nAF:86:938 PHOTO FILE   SCAN 077    PICTURE 1175 ATF#1175', 'A PICTURE OF A WEDDING COUPLE', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'a-picture-of-a-wedding-couple', '', '', '2017-07-03 23:59:07', '2017-07-03 23:59:07', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8080/wp/?post_type=item&#038;p=958', 0, 'item', '', 0),
