(998, 1, '2017-07-04 00:22:03', '2017-07-04 00:22:03', '\"J. ESTEY &amp; CO. BRATTELBORO VT. MANUFACTURER OF THE ESTEY COTTAGE ORGAN BRATTELBORO VT. #33O92 PATENTES DATES LISTED - SV MARCH 1872 BY..(CAN\'T READ) - T BY .. C L.O. T -\r\nTYPED IN ORIGINAL BOOK: \"BROUGHT TO UTAH IN 1852 BY JOHN &amp; CATHERINE CREER SINGLETON. LATER WAS IN THE HOME OF JOHN ALME &amp; SARAH JANE FILES SINGLETON. CATHERINE WORTHEN, THEIR DESCENDENT, TRADED IT TO GILBERT JOHN BAXTER AS PART PAYMENT ON WORK. MR. BAXTER PRESENTED IT TO THE D.U.P. JULY 10, 1958. IT IS BEING USED NOW AT D.U.P. MEETINGS\" ABOVE HISTORICAL IS INCORECT AS MANUFACTURERS LABLE INSIDE INDICATES MARCH 1872 AS LATEST DATE.\r\nNOTE: RONDA MARSHAL SAYS THIS ORGAN FELL OUT OF THE WAGON WHILE COMMING ACROSS THE PLAINS AND WAS BROKEN. IT WAS REPAIRED AND PLAYED FOR MANY YEARS. (MERIANNE NELSON 1994)\r\nGIVEN BY GILBERT JOHN BAXTER THE AMERICAN FORK NEWSPAPER DATED AUGUST 14,1958 HAD THE FOLLOWING ARTICLE ALONG WITH A PICTURE OF JOHN GILBERT BAXTER, MRS. NELLIE BASSETT, MRS. LUELLA BINNS, MRS. MYRTLE SEASTRAND , MR. AND MRS. BAXTER AND MRS. MABLE ADAMSON. “THE DAUGHTERS OF UTAH PIONEERS WERE RECIPIENTS OF AN ORGAN RECENTLY, PRESENTED TO THEM BY JOHN GILBERT BAXTER OF AMERICAN FORK, TO BE PLACED IN THE NEWLY CONTRUCTED RELIC HALL.\r\nTHE ORGAN WAS FIRST PURCHASED IN 1852 BY UTAH PIONEERS, JOHN AND CATHERINE CREER SINGLETON. IT REMAINED IN THE PARLOR OF THE OLD SINGLETON HOME OCCUPIED BY DESCENDANTS, UNTIL 1945 WHEN MR. BAXTER PURCHASED IT.\r\nLUELLA MOYLE BINNS, WIFE OF THE LATE THOMAS BINNS, A GRAND SON OF THE SINGLETON\'S CALLED ON MR. BAXTER RECENTLY AND STATED A WISH TO OBTAIN THE ORGAN FOR THE DUP RELIC HALL. ON JULY 10 MR. BAXTER DONATED THE ORGAN TO THE DUP AND AT THIS TIME IT WAS PLACED IN THE RELIC HALL.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8080/wp/?attachment_id=997\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-997\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-997\" src=\"http://localhost:8080/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/rsz_atf70-30