(1016, 1, '2017-07-04 02:54:51', '2017-07-04 02:54:51', 'ORNATE GOLD FRAME IS 1 ½ INCHES WIDE. HANDWORK DONE ON A BACKGROUND FABRIC THAT IS BLACK. FIVE LARGE FLOWERS OF YARN ARE RED, VARIGARED RED AND WHITE AND THREE ALL WHITE YEARN. OTHER YARN COLORS INCLUDE LIGHT BLUE, TURQUOISE,GREEN AND FAN. FERNLIKE STICHES SURROUND THE CENTER CHENILE FLOWERS. ON THE LABEL: WOOL EMBOIDERED PICTURE MADE BY SARAH HOLT ROBINSON BORN 6 MARCH 1804 IN SALFORD, LANCASTER, ENGLAND. DAUGHTER OF JAMES HOLT AND MARTHA WALKER. MARRIED IN 1824 TO GEORGE ROBINSON. SHE CAME TO UTAH AND TO AMERICAN FORK IN 1852. SHE DIED 7 JULY 1896. CHILDREN OF SARAH INCLUDE: JOSEPH, WILLIAM, ELIZA (PEET), SAMUEL, ELIZABETH, THANKFUL (SHELLEY). PICTURE GIVEN BY EDNA SHELLEY HOCKSTRASSED. GREAT GRAND DAUGHTER.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8080/wp/item/framed-emboidery-work-with-yarn/rsz_atf553/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1017\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1017\" src=\"http://localhost:8080/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/rsz_atf553-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\r\n\r\nAF:88:958 SOUTH WALL PICTURE 553 ATF#553', 'FRAMED EMBOIDERY WORK WITH YARN', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'framed-emboidery-work-with-yarn', '', '', '2017-07-04 02:54:53', '2017-07-04 02:54:53', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8080/wp/?post_type=item&#038;p=1016', 0, 'item', '', 0),
